1. Categories of personal data we collect
We collect data you provide voluntarily (e.g., reading preferences, name, email), data from third parties (e.g., Google sign-in data), and data automatically collected (e.g., IP address).
2. Purposes for processing personal data
We process your personal data for various purposes, including providing our Services, customizing your experience, managing your account, communicating with you, providing customer support, analyzing usage, and serving ads.
3. Legal bases for processing (EEA-based users)
We process personal data based on consent, contract performance, legitimate interests, and compliance with legal obligations.
4. Data sharing
We share data with third-party service providers, law enforcement agencies, public authorities, and during business transactions like mergers or acquisitions.
5. Exercising your privacy rights
You have rights to access, review, update, correct, delete, or restrict the use of your personal data. EEA-based users have additional rights, including data portability and lodging complaints with supervisory authorities.
6. Age limitation
We do not knowingly process personal data from persons under 16 years of age. If you learn that someone under 16 has provided us with personal data, contact us at
support@wiserapp.co
.
7. International data transfers
We transfer personal data globally, deploying safeguards like Standard Contractual Clauses or relying on adequacy decisions.
8. Changes to this Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy. Material changes will be communicated through our Services or other available means.
9. Supplemental notice for California residents
California residents have rights under the CCPA, including knowing what personal information is collected and disclosed, and opting out of the sale of personal information.
10. Supplemental notice for Virginia residents
Virginia residents have rights under the VCDPA, including accessing, correcting, and deleting personal data, and opting out of targeted advertising.
11. Supplemental notice for Nevada residents
Nevada residents can opt-out of the sale of personal information. Currently, we do not sell personal information as defined by Nevada law.
12. Account deletion
You can delete your account using the ‚ÄúSettings‚Äù function in the App or Website, or by contacting us at
support@wiserapp.co
.
13. Data retention
We retain personal data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy and comply with legal obligations.
14. Handling ‚ÄúDo Not Track‚Äù requests
Our App does not support ‚ÄúDo Not Track‚Äù requests. Check third-party services‚Äô privacy policies to see if they honor such requests.
15. Personal data controller
HubX, located at 71-75 Shelton St, Covent Garden, London WC2H 9JQ, GB, will be the controller of your personal data.
16. Contact us
